---
// Aesop section: the orchestration harness that ships its own features
// Component contract: no props, system fonts only, tokens.css custom properties
---

<section class="aesop-section">
  <p class="section-moral">
    <em>The fox measured twice and paid for one architecture.</em>
  </p>

  <h2 id="aesop">Aesop — the system that builds itself</h2>

  <div class="aesop-pitch">
    <p>
      Open-source orchestration harness for Claude Code that ships its own features via parallel agent fleets. Cheap Haiku workers on scoped domains, a lean orchestrator on durable git-committed state: <strong>130 of its own PRs implemented, tested, and merged by its wave cycle.</strong>
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="https://github.com/matt82198/aesop" class="cta-link">github.com/matt82198/aesop</a>
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="architecture-section">
    <h3>Architecture highlights</h3>
    <ul class="architecture-list">
      <li>
        <strong>Haiku-first dispatch</strong> — measured ~1/3 the cost, A/B-validated
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Event-sourced SQLite</strong> (WAL) state store with git demoted to rendered export
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Watchdog daemon</strong> — secret-scan pre-push gate + heartbeat liveness
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>React 18 + Vite dashboard</strong> — real-time SSE updates, no frame rate lock
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Read-only MCP server</strong> for fleet status querying
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>One-turn wave workflow</strong> — backlog → parallel build → verify → merge train
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="scars-section">
    <h3>Scars, documented</h3>
    <div class="scars-list">
      <div class="scar-item">
        <div class="scar-title">Hierarchical dispatch cost trap</div>
        <p>
          A/B test showed Sonnet-specialist dispatch cost 4.3× for identical quality. Architecture cancelled, data kept — the measurement became more valuable than the experiment.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="scar-item">
        <div class="scar-title">CI union-drift bug</div>
        <p>
          Every PR green against its own base while main still broke. The commit gate saw disjoint test runs. Fixed with branch-protection + drift gates; now a baseline check for any distributed CI.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="scar-item">
        <div class="scar-title">Fail-open lock timeout</div>
        <p>
          500ms lock timeout proceeded unlocked, silently dropping writes. Root-caused and moved to an event-sourced store where every mutation is ordered and auditable.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="numbers-section">
    <h3>By the numbers</h3>
    <div class="numbers-table">
      <div class="numbers-row">
        <span class="numbers-label">Commits</span>
        <span class="numbers-value">354</span>
      </div>
      <div class="numbers-row">
        <span class="numbers-label">PRs merged</span>
        <span class="numbers-value">130</span>
      </div>
      <div class="numbers-row">
        <span class="numbers-label">Waves</span>
        <span class="numbers-value">13</span>
      </div>
      <div class="numbers-row">
        <span class="numbers-label">Domains</span>
        <span class="numbers-value">14</span>
      </div>
      <div class="numbers-row">
        <span class="numbers-label">Test files</span>
        <span class="numbers-value">46</span>
      </div>
      <div class="numbers-row">
        <span class="numbers-label">LOC</span>
        <span class="numbers-value">52.6K</span>
      </div>
      <div class="numbers-row">
        <span class="numbers-label">Version</span>
        <span class="numbers-value">v0.1.0-beta.4</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="numbers-note">
      <em>Every number computed from git, reproducible by cloning.</em>
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .aesop-section {
    margin: var(--space-16) 0;
  }

  .section-moral {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-tertiary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
    line-height: var(--leading-normal);
  }

  .section-moral em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-text-tertiary);
  }

  .aesop-section h2 {
    font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
    line-height: var(--leading-tight);
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    scroll-margin-top: 80px;
  }

  .aesop-section h3 {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-top: var(--space-12);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
    line-height: var(--leading-tight);
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
  }

  .aesop-pitch {
    max-width: var(--width-prose);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
  }

  .aesop-pitch p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .aesop-pitch strong {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .cta-link {
    display: inline-block;
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--accent);
    transition: color var(--duration-fast) var(--ease-out),
                border-color var(--duration-fast) var(--ease-out),
                background-color var(--duration-fast) var(--ease-out);
    padding: var(--space-1) var(--space-2);
    margin: calc(var(--space-1) * -1) calc(var(--space-2) * -1);
    border-radius: 2px;
  }

  .cta-link:hover {
    color: var(--accent-light);
    border-bottom-color: var(--accent-light);
    background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
  }

  .cta-link:focus {
    outline: var(--focus-ring);
    outline-offset: var(--focus-ring-offset);
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .cta-link {
      transition: none;
    }
  }

  .architecture-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
  }

  .architecture-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  .architecture-list li {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    padding-left: var(--space-6);
    position: relative;
  }

  .architecture-list li::before {
    content: "→";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .architecture-list strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .scars-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
  }

  .scars-list {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-8);
  }

  .scar-item {
    padding: var(--space-6);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .scar-title {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
  }

  .scar-item p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .numbers-section {
    margin-top: var(--space-16);
  }

  .numbers-table {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    background-color: var(--color-code-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 4px;
    overflow: hidden;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }

  .numbers-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-6);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    align-items: center;
  }

  .numbers-row:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .numbers-label {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .numbers-value {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-align: right;
  }

  .numbers-note {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-tertiary);
    line-height: var(--leading-normal);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .numbers-note em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-text-tertiary);
  }

  /* Responsive: stack numbers table for narrow screens */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .numbers-row {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: var(--space-2);
    }

    .numbers-value {
      text-align: left;
    }
  }
</style>
